#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput

#variableConversion

locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring"))

#variableConversion
abs(locationX)
abs
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.goto(locationX LocationY)

t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring"))

#variableConversion
locationX abs(locationX)
abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)

t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown(
turtle.filcolor("black")
)
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
centRad *= 4
turtle.circl
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#outermostRing

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.penup()

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing


#hide&keep

t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing



#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
7259-Removed: 10
event                     e
input                   NaN
removed                  \n
cursor_pos            623.0
timestamp     1612212113775
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7259, dtype: object

import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color(b)


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
07303-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     l
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            635.0
timestamp     1612212143392
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7303, dtype: object
************************************************

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pe


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
tur


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
07474-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     u
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            716.0
timestamp     1612212220255
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7474, dtype: object
************************************************

centRad *= 4

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.en


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
07517-Input: 5
event                     e
input                 _fill
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            727.0
timestamp     1612212226726
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7517, dtype: object

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.p


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                     e
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            743.0
timestamp     1612212235750
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7554, dtype: object

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
centRad = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                     c
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            628.0
timestamp     1612212285403

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
locationY = abs(locationY)
cent = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(locationX,locationY)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

removed                   t
cursor_pos            389.0

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
locationX = abs(locationX)
loca= abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(locationX,locationY)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
7670-Removed: 10
event                     e
input                   NaN
removed                   a
cursor_pos            362.0
timestamp     1612212380323
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7670, dtype: object

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
 = abs(locationX)
yPos= abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locationY)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(locationX,locationY)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                   NaN
removed                  \n
cursor_pos            331.0
timestamp     1612212388886

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(locationX, locat)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(locationX,locationY)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
7746-Removed: 10
event                     e
input                   NaN
removed                   t
cursor_pos            460.0
timestamp     1612212408991
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7746, dtype: object

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(locationX,locationY)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                     y
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            450.0
timestamp     1612212416211
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7783, dtype: object

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
ce *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(locationX,locationY)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

removed                   e
cursor_pos            516.0

import turtle

#userInput

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(locat)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
centRad *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
R *= 3/4
turtle.circle(centRad)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
07901-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     a
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            679.0
timestamp     1612212449674
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7901, dtype: object

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 3/4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 3/4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                    \n
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            598.0
timestamp     1612212492163
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7942, dtype: object

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#defi
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 3/4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
07980-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     n
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            603.0
timestamp     1612212510464
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 7980, dtype: object
************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefingi
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 3/4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
8019-Removed: 10
event                     e
input                   NaN
removed                   i
cursor_pos            607.0
timestamp     1612212516791
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8019, dtype: object

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
R

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 3/4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08057-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     a
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            620.0
timestamp     1612212529910
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8057, dtype: object

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
xPos 
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
y po
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
8133-Removed: 10
event                     e
input                   NaN
removed                   o
cursor_pos            636.0
timestamp     1612212602328
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8133, dtype: object
************************************************

yPos += 1
#drawingRing

turtle.color("blue")

yPos += (1/4)*r

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/4)*R
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08178-Input: 5
event                     e
input                 adius
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            648.0
timestamp     1612212634714
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8178, dtype: object

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLoc
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/)*Radius
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08213-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     a
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            431.0
timestamp     1612212807272
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8213, dtype: object

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/)*Radius
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 *
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/)*Radius
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#draw
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (3/4) * Radius
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

input                     i
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            462.0

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawi
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables

yPos += (3/4) * Radius
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()

turtle.end_fill()

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (/4) * Radius
#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08327-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     #
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            859.0
timestamp     1612215090307
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8327, dtype: object

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#se
#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#sec
#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            863.0

locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#r

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08398-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     e
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            877.0
timestamp     1612215121318
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8398, dtype: object

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variabl

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            894.0

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos +

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08500-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     d
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            936.0
timestamp     1612215178383
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8500, dtype: object
************************************************

Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
Turt

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08532-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     l
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            952.0
timestamp     1612215184810
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8532, dtype: object

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

import turtle

#userInput

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

yPos = abs(locationY)

#definingLocation

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.c

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turt

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08627-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     l
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos            995.0
timestamp     1612215208701
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8627, dtype: object

#userInput

Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.pendown()

Radius *= 4

yPos += (1/3) * Radius

Radius = centDiameter / 2

#definingLocation

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendow

#hide&keep

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.pendown()

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
tu

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

yPos = abs(locationY)

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()

turtle.end_fill()

turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
t

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
tu

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(R)

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

removed                 NaN

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius
              turtle.end_fill()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

input                     )
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1080.0

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turt
#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08769-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     l
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1072.0
timestamp     1612215250857
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8769, dtype: object
************************************************

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup(

)
#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

turtle.done()

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#center

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerR

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08829-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     i
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1092.0
timestamp     1612215523356
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8829, dtype: object
************************************************

import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
08858-Input: 1
event                     e
input                    \n
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1098.0
timestamp     1612215530803
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 8858, dtype: object
************************************************

#userInput

turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

Radius *= 4

turtle.end_fill()

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#Redefining

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

removed                   g
cursor_pos           1107.0

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()

turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#rede

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

input                     n
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1102.0
timestamp     1612215546278

#userInput

#outermostRing

#definingLocation

#drawingRing

turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefining

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

input                     V
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1108.0
timestamp     1612215550863
file               task2.py

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningV

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables

#dr

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables

#dra

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#userInput

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

yPos = abs(locationY)

Radius *= 4

turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius 

#drawingRing

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *

#drawingRing

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")

Radius *= 4

turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos+= 

#drawingRing

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos+= Radius

#drawingRing
tur

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
09054-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     t
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1163.0
timestamp     1612215637616
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN

Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos+= Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.g

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos+= Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.go

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
