import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos+= Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
t

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
09107-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     u
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1184.0
timestamp     1612215651936
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 9107, dtype: object
************************************************

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

Radius *= 4

turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#redefiningVariables

yPos += (1/3) * Radius

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.penup()
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color('red')
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos+= Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                     "
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1196.0
timestamp     1612215656933
file               task2.py

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos+= Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")


#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                     t
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1206.0
timestamp     1612215671029
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN

#moduleImport
import turtle

locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing



#definingLocation
yPos += 4 * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

turtle.pendown()

yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")b
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################
010128-Input: 1
event                     e
input                     n
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1043.0
timestamp     1612217885176
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 10128, dtype: object

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)

#definingLocation
yPos -= 4 * Radius
Radius *= 4
#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")bn
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter

#definingLocation

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos, yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter
turtle.goto(xPos, yPos)

#definingLocation
yPos -= 4 * Radius
Radius *= 4
#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos, yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

# @@@@@ @@@@@@@@@@
# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)

#definingLocation
yPos -= 4 * Radius
Radius *= 4
#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

event                     e
input                     b
removed                 NaN
cursor_pos           1042.0
timestamp     1612218828778
file               task2.py
ver                     NaN
Name: 10248, dtype: object

import turtle

#userInput

locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))

turtle.end_fill()

yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.pendown()

turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")b
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()

turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion

yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)

#definingLocation
yPos -= 4 * Radius
Radius *= 4
#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")b
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)

#definingLocation
Radius *= 4
yPos -= 4 * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos -= (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos -= (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos -= Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
t("please enter location of center (x,y) - ")************************************************
###########################################################

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)

#definingLocation
Radius *= 4
yPos -= 4 * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos = Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()

# CS1400 - CO1
# Assignment 2

#moduleImport
import turtle

#userInput
locationX = int(input("Please enter x value for center of target - "))
locationY = int(input("Please enter y value for center of target - "))
centDiameter = float(input("please enter desired diameter of center ring - "))

#variableConversion
xPos = abs(locationX)
yPos = abs(locationY)
Radius = centDiameter / 2

#outermostRing

#goingToCenter
#movingToCenter
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)

#definingLocation
Radius *= 4
yPos -= 4 * Radius

#drawingRing

turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.pendown()
turtle.color("black")
turtle.begin_fill()
Radius *= 4
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#tertiaryRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 3/4
yPos += (1/3) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("blue")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#secondaryRing

#redefining variables
Radius *= 2/3
yPos += (1/2) * Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("red")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#centerRing

#redefiningVariables
Radius *= 1/2
yPos += Radius

#drawingRing
turtle.goto(xPos,yPos)
turtle.color("yellow")
turtle.pendown()
turtle.begin_fill()
turtle.circle(Radius)
turtle.end_fill()
turtle.penup()

#hide&keep
turtle.hideturtle()
turtle.done()
